# SecondMe OAuth Configuration — DO NOT MODIFY

The following values are issued by the SecondMe platform and must NEVER be changed by AI or automation:

## Protected values in `.env` / `.env.local`
- `SECONDME_CLIENT_ID` — registered app identifier
- `SECONDME_CLIENT_SECRET` — issued by SecondMe Developer Console
- `SECONDME_REDIRECT_URI` — must match Developer Console registration
- `SECONDME_OAUTH_URL` — SecondMe platform constant
- `SECONDME_TOKEN_ENDPOINT` — SecondMe platform constant
- `SECONDME_API_BASE_URL` — SecondMe platform constant

## Protected files
- `.secondme/state.json` — platform-generated app config, read-only
- `src/lib/auth.ts` — OAuth flow functions (`getAuthorizationUrl`, `exchangeCodeForToken`, `refreshAccessToken`, `callSecondMeAPI`). Field mappings in these functions reflect the actual SecondMe API response format and must not be changed without verifying against the live API.

## When working with auth
- If authentication fails, check server logs first — do NOT guess or change OAuth parameters
- If field names need updating, verify against actual SecondMe API response (add `console.log` temporarily)
- Reference docs: https://develop-docs.second.me/zh/docs/authentication/oauth2
